{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"pitcher with narrow spout or funnel pitcher, slotted or spherification spoon, paper towels, champagne flutes, transparent plastic container, plastic container with lid, refrigerator, freezer","id":"r416625","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-CGnHTYPX37U\/XZMvvxTVeFI\/AAAAAAAAaVs\/8w7q84Ipx9gq2VjeRJOXRij7Z-x1DQooACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_oNod5apB5x2IF0xv.png","title":"Concord Grape Pearls with Champagne (Bill Yosses)","publishedAt":"2019-03-29T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"16 oz canola oil, cold"},{"content":"4 oz water"},{"content":"¾ tsp agar-agar powder"},{"content":"6 oz grape juice concentrate, Concord"},{"content":"¼ tsp locust bean gum"},{"content":"1 bottle champagne"}],"nutrition":{},"preparations":[{"content":"Place a transparent plastic container (gel will stick to metal or glass) onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in cold oil. Place in freezer and chill 5 minutes or until ready to use."},{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl and heat <b>2 min 30 sec\/212°F\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add agar-agar by sprinkling around edge of mixing bowl avoiding the blades and cook <b>15 sec\/212°F\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add grape juice concentrate and without measuring cup cook <b>2 min\/212°F\/speed 2<b>, while slowly sprinkling locust gum through hole in mixing bowl lid. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl and blades with spatula, insert measuring cup and cook <b>15 sec\/212°F\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Pour grape juice mixture into a pitcher with a narrow spout. Slowly and carefully, tilt pitcher over oil in cold plastic container so that small droplets fall into the oil. Uniformly sized droplets give a better result. Let droplets rest for 3 minutes to gel."},{"content":"With a large spoon or spherification spoon, carefully remove grape pearls from oil and allow to drain on paper towels. Transfer to a plastic container with lid and refrigerate until ready to use. Store in refrigerator up to five days."},{"content":"Place ½ tsp grape pearls into each of six champagne flutes, pour 6 oz champagne into each glass and serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Recipe makes enough pearls for 30 drinks."],"basicInfo":["advanced","35m","40m","6 portions"]}